      • setViewGroup

        ConsentLib.BuildStep setViewGroup(android.view.ViewGroup v)
        Optional Sets the view group in which WebView will will be rendered into. If it's not called or called with null, the MainView will be used instead. In case the main view is not a ViewGroup, a BuildException will be thrown during when build() is called.
        Parameters:
        v - - the view group
        Returns:
        BuildStep - the next build step
        See Also:
        ConsentLib.BuildStep, ConsentLibException.BuildException, build

      • setOnMessageChoiceSelect

        Parameters:
        c - - a callback that will be called when the user selects an option on the WebView
        Returns:
        BuildStep - the next build step
        See Also:
        ConsentLib.BuildStep, ConsentLib.Callback

      • setOnInteractionComplete

        ConsentLib.BuildStep setOnInteractionComplete(ConsentLib.Callback c)
        Optional Sets the Callback to be called when the user finishes interacting with the WebView either by closing it, canceling or accepting the terms. At this point, the following keys will available populated in the sharedStorage:
        • ConsentLib.EU_CONSENT_KEY
        • ConsentLib.CONSENT_UUID_KEY
        • ConsentLib.IAB_CONSENT_SUBJECT_TO_GDPR
        • ConsentLib.IAB_CONSENT_CONSENT_STRING
        • ConsentLib.IAB_CONSENT_PARSED_PURPOSE_CONSENTS
        • ConsentLib.IAB_CONSENT_PARSED_VENDOR_CONSENTS
        Also at this point, the methods ConsentLib.getCustomVendorConsents(java.lang.String[], com.example.cmplibrary.ConsentLib.OnLoadComplete), ConsentLib.getPurposeConsents(com.example.cmplibrary.ConsentLib.OnLoadComplete) and ConsentLib.getPurposeConsent(java.lang.String, com.example.cmplibrary.ConsentLib.OnLoadComplete) will also be able to be called from inside the callback.
        Parameters:
        c - - Callback to be called when the user finishes interacting with the WebView
        Returns:
        BuildStep - the next build step
        See Also:
        ConsentLib.BuildStep, ConsentLib.Callback

      • build

        ConsentLib build()
          throws ConsentLibException.BuildException
        Run internal tasks and build the ConsentLib. This method will validate the data coming from the previous BuildSteps and throw ConsentLibException.BuildException in case something goes wrong.
        Returns:
        ConsentLib
        Throws:
        ConsentLibException.BuildException - - if any of the required data is missing or invalid
